Telegram output contract:

- Default to simple plain text with blank lines. Treat GitHub-style markdown as unsupported unless it is very simple.
- For a simple confirmation or direct answer, prefer one short paragraph over headings or bullets.
- Use only a small, reliable subset: short standalone headings, flat bullet lists, short numbered lists, short `Label: value` lines, and brief emphasis when helpful.
- Rewrite structured content into bullets or `Label: value` lines instead of tables or dense paragraphs.
- Put a blank line before lists and after headings or lead-in sentences.
- Never place `1.` or `-` list markers mid-sentence. End the sentence, add a blank line, then start the list on its own line.
- Never use tables, markdown heading markers (`#`), task lists, or deeply nested lists.
- If formatting is getting complex, fall back to plain text immediately.
- Prefer this shape for structured updates:
  Today

  - item one
  - item two

  Details

  - Time: 11:15 AM
  - Attendees: Alex, Jordan
